	  is an open book.</figDesc>
	</figure>
	--></div><pb facs="page_image16"/><div><head>C<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>CHARLOTTE</head><lg><l>THE luckiest child I know is<lb/>Charlotte—</l><l>Her Mother dresses her in<lb/>scarlet.</l></lg><pb facs="page_image17"/>
        <!--
	<figure>
	  <head>C</head>
	  <figDesc>A girl in a scarlet coat and hat holding a green balloon.</figDesc>
	</figure>
 --></div><pb facs="page_image18"/><div><head>D<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>DAN</head><lg><l>OH, a brown legged Gypsy Boy<lb/>is Dan.</l><l>He rides in a white-topped<lb/>Caravan.</l><l>He can't tell his letters which<lb/>from which,</l><l>But he can turn handsprings<lb/>in any ditch!</l></lg><pb facs="page_image19"/><ab>D</ab></div><pb facs="page_image20"/><div><head>E<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>ELIZA</head><lg><l>A SOLEMN child is small Eliza;</l><l>Each day she grows a little<lb/>wiser</l></lg><pb facs="page_image21"/><ab>E</ab></div><pb facs="page_image22"/><div><head>F<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>FERDINAND</head><lg><l>GREEDY little Ferdinand</l><l>Has ice-cream comes in either<lb/>hand.</l></lg><pb facs="page_image23"/><ab>F</ab></div><pb facs="page_image24"/><div><head>G<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>GRACE</head><lg><l>GRACE can dance upon her<lb/>toes.</l><l>How she learned to no one<lb/>knows.</l><l>Maybe friendly Brownies<lb/>taught her.</l><l>Or the Kind of Elfland's<lb/>daughter!</l></lg><pb facs="page_image25"/><ab>G</ab></div><pb facs="page_image26"/><div><head>H<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>HENRY</head><lg><l>HENRY and his puppy share</l><l>This gay quilt, the lucky pair!</l></lg><pb facs="page_image27"/><ab>H</ab></div><pb facs="page_image28"/><div><head>I<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>ISABEL</head><lg><l>ISABEL could sew and sing;</l><l>She could do most everything</l><l>Excepr just this, poor Isabel</l><l>Never <hi rend="italic">could</hi> learn how to spell.</l></lg><pb facs="page_image29"/><ab>I</ab></div><pb facs="page_image30"/><div><head>J<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>JIM</head><lg><l>JIM!Jim!</l><l>Come out and swim.</l><l>Fill your pail up</l><l>To the brim.</l><l>Roll in sand</l><l>And splash in sea</l><l>From breakfast till</l><l>It's time for tea!</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image31"/><pb facs="page_image32"/><div><head>K<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>KITTY</head><lg><l>ALL dress in apple green<lb/>goes Kitty,</l><l>A-walking up and down the<lb/>City.</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image33"/><pb facs="page_image34"/><div><head>L<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>LUIGI</head><lg><l>LUIGI'S father is so kind:</l><l>He often lets Luigu grind,</l><l>Or pass the monkey's cup of<lb/>tin</l><l>And count the pennies that<lb/>come in</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image35"/><pb facs="page_image36"/><div><head>M<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>MAY</head><lg><l>OH, MAY'S the sweetest month<lb/>of Spring</l><l>With flowers to bloom and<lb/>birds to sing;</l><l>But Molly, Meg, and Marjorie</l><l>Are sweeter far to hear and<lb/>see,</l><l>Playing on the flower-strewn<lb/>green</l><l>Each in turn a May Day<lb/>Queen.</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image37"/><pb facs="page_image38"/><div><head>N<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>NED</head><lg><l>BATH is over; prayers are<lb/>said</l><l>Ned is on his way to bed!</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image39"/><pb facs="page_image40"/><div><head>O<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>OLIVE</head><lg><l>OLIVE dust the parlor;</l><l>Olive sweep the floor;</l><l>Brush away the cobwebs</l><l>Behind the pantry door!</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image41"/><pb facs="page_image42"/><div><head>P<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>PETER PAN</head><lg><l>OH, PETER PAN was the boy<lb/>who could</l><l>Play on his pipe in a leafy<lb/>wood.</l><l>Beasts and Bunnies brown<lb/>crept near him,</l><l>And all the birds grew still to<lb/>hear him.</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image43"/><pb facs="page_image44"/><div><head>Q<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>QUAKER</head><lg><l>THIS Quaker child of Quality</l><l>Lived in another century,</l><l>Dressed all in gray with ker-<lb/>chief neat,</l><l>She trod Nantucket's long<lb/>Main street;</l><l>Climbed to the roof walk;<lb/>heard the din</l><l>Of square-rigged whalers sail-<lb/>ing in.</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image45"/><pb facs="page_image46"/><div><head>R<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>ROGER</head><lg><l>NEARLY always, Roger goes</l><l>Slipping, sliding on his toes,</l><l>Over ice and cobblestones.</l><l>People tremble for his bones!</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image47"/><pb facs="page_image48"/><div><head>S<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>SOPHIA</head><lg><l>SOPHIA'S picking raspberries;</l><l>Her basket's green and new;</l><l>The raspberries are crimson,</l><l>Her hands and lips are too!</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image49"/><pb facs="page_image50"/><div><head>I<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>TIMOTHY</head><lg><l>TIME for tea,<lb/>Timothy;</l><l>Kettle's humming<lb/>Cozily;</l><l>Toast and jam <lb/>For you and Me!</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image51"/><pb facs="page_image52"/><div><head>U<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>UNA</head><lg><l>UNA loves to carry things--</l><l>Paper parcels tied with strings,</l><l>Bags and bundles fascinate<lb/>her,</l><l>Shopping does not irritate<lb/>her.</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image53"/><pb facs="page_image54"/><div><head>V<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>VINCENT</head><lg><l>LITTLE Vincent Vanderpool</l><l>Cannot bear to go to school,</l><l>Any day he'll leave his books</l><l>For woods and fields and<lb/>wading-brooks.</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image55"/><pb facs="page_image56"/><div><head>W<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>WINNIE</head><lg><l>PINK of cheek and brown of<lb/>eye,</l><l>Winnie's sweet, but rather<lb/>shy.</l><l>Once she brought me tulips<lb/>gay</l><l>From her house across the<lb/>way.</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image57"/><pb facs="page_image58"/><div><head>X<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>LITTLE X</head><lg><l>X IS the little unknown boy</l><l>I passed at the crossroads<lb/>sign;</l><l>He didn't tell his name to me,</l><l>I didn't tell him mine!</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image59"/><pb facs="page_image60"/><div><head>Y<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>YETTA</head><lg><l>YETTA lives across the sea</l><l>In a place called Italy.</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image61"/><pb facs="page_image62"/><div><head>Z<lb/>IS FOR<lb/>ZACHARY</head><lg><l>ZACHARY is not to blame</l><l>For having such an awful<lb/>name.</l></lg></div><pb facs="page_image63"/><pb facs="page_image64"/><pb facs="page_image65"/><pb facs="page_image66"/><pb facs="page_image67"/><pb facs="page_image68"/><pb facs="page_image69"/><pb facs="page_image70"/><pb facs="page_image71" type="innerbackcover"/><note>Parents  .  .  .  .<lb/>Send for out 